-- pd.package: FTD karma package
name: fastn-community.github.io/karma

This FTD font `karma` package is for your ftd web projects. To Use this
karma inside `FTD` project follow below instructions.

-- ds.h3: How to use karma?

-- ds.code: Add this to your FASTN.ftd
lang: ftd

\-- fastn.dependency: fastn-community.github.io/karma

-- ds.markdown: 

After adding karma dependency inside your `FASTN.ftd` file, You need to
add karma assets and import it inside your `.ftd` files where you are
using this font for your custom font types. 

To include karma into your `ftd` file follow below instructions.

-- ds.code:
lang: ftd

\-- import: fastn-community.github.io/karma/assets as karma-assets


-- ds.h3: How to create a custom karma type? 

-- ds.markdown: 

We don't recommend creating custom types. We recommend to use 
our [karma-typography](https://fastn-community.github.io/karma-typography)

If you're using [karma-typography](https://fastn-community.github.io/karma-typography) 
and still your designer has introduced new font size which are not included or 
part of our [karma-typography](https://fastn-community.github.io/karma-typography) 
then only define custom types. 

We hope you shouldn't need to define a custom type.

Below is an example of creating a custom `ftd.type` using karma.

-- ds.rendered:

-- ds.rendered.input:

\-- ftd.type karma-size-12-desktop:
size.px: 12
weight: 400
font-family: $karma-assets.fonts.Karma


\-- ftd.type karma-size-12-mobile:
size.px: 12
weight: 400
font-family: $karma-assets.fonts.Karma

\-- ftd.responsive-type karma-size-12-400:
desktop: $karma-size-12-desktop
mobile: $karma-size-12-mobile

\-- ftd.text: 
role: $karma-size-12-400
color: $inherited.colors.text-strong

`font-size: 12px, font-weight: 400` 

